7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Cleanvoice and Krisp share a solid foundation of core features including Noise Removal. Where Cleanvoice pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Podcast Editing and Multilingual and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Krisp uniquely offers Speech To Text and Real Time, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Cleanvoice holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Krisp scores 8/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Krisp comes in at a lower starting price of $8/mo, while Cleanvoice begins at $10/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Cleanvoice's free tier and Krisp's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
